1
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:11,680
By everyone who received the white envelope...

2
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:13,680
...will get to act in the new Glamorous Airline commercial.

3
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:18,800
Who’s the teacher?

4
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:23,320
This is Ms. Dina and Ms. Piangduan, who will be leading the workshop today.

5
00:01:23,320 --> 00:01:24,280
Aren’t they enemies?

6
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:26,840
I didn’t outshine you, did I, Dina?

7
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:28,840
Choose. This or that?

8
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:33,640
Someone put glass shards in my shoes.

9
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:35,880
You think I don’t know it was you?

10
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:38,640
Yes. I hate you.

11
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:45,880
Announcement from Mr. Glam.

12
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:49,040
Announcement of changes from the airline.

13
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:51,800
Does this mean Mr. Glam just got here?

14
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:54,080
Maybe he rode a motorbike taxi to stick this up.

15
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:56,320
He probably climbed up and posted it himself...

16
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:58,840
No, he is the owner of the airline!

17
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:00,840
He would have had the staff post it!

18
00:02:01,960 --> 00:02:04,600
Come on, let’s listen together.

19
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:07,320
Announcement of changes from the airline.

20
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:11,320
Glamorous Airline has a policy to adjust its corporate image.

21
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:14,320
Erase all the negative image from the past.

22
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:15,760
By doing...

23
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:16,760
What the hell...

24
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:19,320
Huh?

25
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:26,040
Has our company switched to using white envelopes?

26
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:27,960
Oh no, do you know what a white envelope means?

27
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:28,960
This kind of white envelope.

28
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:32,720
Oh, to collect donations in the temple envelope?

29
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:35,560
Then go with the monk, please.

30
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:36,960
Maybe, they're for other people.

31
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:37,960
Tid-Gift.

32
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:40,960
All-New.

33
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:43,560
Kreetha.

34
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:46,120
Chaba.

35
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:48,440
Chai.

36
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:50,840
Sky.

37
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:56,520
That’s not true, we haven’t finished reading yet.

38
00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:00,640
Erase all the negative image from the past.

39
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:03,680
By making a new commercial.

40
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:05,680
See? They’re not firing anyone.

41
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:11,120
Maybe they’re making ads to recruit new flight attendants?

42
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:16,600
That’s not true, I only secretly ate passenger food on the plane.

43
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:18,160
Do I really have to get fired for that?

44
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:21,400
From now on, I will not pretend to be working.

45
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:24,520
But actually just walk around...

46
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:27,520
Sky, are you packing already?

47
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:32,160
I’m returning the first-class items.

48
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:34,160
So maybe they’ll see that I’ve changed into a better person.

49
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:42,880
CCTVs! CCTVs!

50
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:43,760
Mr. Glam...

51
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:46,560
Mr. Glam is probably watching us through the CCTVs.

52
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:49,520
From now on, I will work hard.

53
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:52,800
Don’t fire me, please.

54
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:55,240
I promise I’ll make myself look less glamorous.

55
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:59,240
And look normal like these kids.

56
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:00,480
Is this the worst?

57
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:04,720
I can’t even think of what I did wrong.

58
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:11,400
Chai, we haven’t finished reading yet.

59
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,400
Should we finish reading first?

60
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:18,040
Erase all the negative image from the past.

61
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,400
By making a new commercial.

62
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:22,520
To give the airline a brighter image.

63
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:24,760
By everyone who received the white envelope...

64
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:26,720
No, I don’t want the white envelope.

65
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:28,960
I don’t want the white envelope, I’m scared.

66
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:31,640
...will get to act in the new Glamorous Airline commercial.

67
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:35,560
What? A new commercial?

68
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:39,280
Congratulations, you’ve been chosen to represent the crew.

69
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:41,280
And appear in our new commercial.

70
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:54,400
Everyone, this means all of us are fired.

71
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,840
Just to be in a commercial?

72
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:57,840
I’ve had enough.

73
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:01,560
You’re really not The Face, Kreetha.

74
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,800
Where’s Sky?

75
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:05,800
Sky, aren’t you happy?

76
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:11,960
Uh, yeah, yeah. Sure.

77
00:05:11,960 --> 00:05:15,520
There was no stealing from first class, right?

78
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:16,720
Yeah, yeah.

79
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:18,680
And nobody secretly ate anything either, right?

80
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:20,720
Because I was just checking if it was spoiled.

81
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:21,040
Right.

82
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:23,040
And no slacking around, right?

83
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:24,600
No, no.

84
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:25,840
This is perfect for us then.

85
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:26,840
Yeah, true.

86
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:29,080
But not Kreetha, he’s dumb.

87
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:30,080
Chaba, you’re harsh.

88
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:57,360
We’re ready.

89
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:11,400
Excuse me, are you the crew?

90
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:12,200
Yes.

91
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:14,440
So where’s our trailer?

92
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:17,200
And please get me mineral water from Mount Kilimanjaro.

93
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:19,200
Kept at thirty-two degrees Celsius.

94
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:22,600
And most importantly, strawberries with no genetic modification.

95
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:25,400
Please pick out all the seeds for me.

96
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:31,400
And finally, I want eucalyptus aroma therapy. That’s all.

97
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:33,920
Aren't I the star?

98
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:39,080
Wow, Kreetha, you look good today.

99
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:40,800
Where did you get that from?

100
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,800
Oh, I borrowed it from Chai.

101
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:45,440
No expectations, no disappointments.

102
00:06:47,280 --> 00:06:50,200
Chai, is our airline broke?

103
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:52,440
Why does this set look so deserted?

104
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:53,440
I don’t know.

105
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:54,840
They're coming.

106
00:06:58,240 --> 00:07:00,240
Is it thirty-two degrees Celsius?

107
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:03,640
It’s room temperature.

108
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:08,920
And the seedless strawberries?

109
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:16,560
And the eucalyptus aroma?

110
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,040
Are we starting the shoot?

111
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:26,480
No, we’re not shooting today.

112
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:28,280
Huh?

113
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:31,280
Today is just a workshop session for everyone.

114
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,000
Oh, I’m so excited, my heart is racing.

115
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,360
Who’s teaching?

116
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,240
Moms are here!

117
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:43,440
So cute, bringing Mom to work.

118
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,440
Stand up.

119
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:12,640
Everyone, this is Ms. Dina and Ms. Piangduan.

120
00:08:12,640 --> 00:08:14,640
They will be leading the workshop today.

121
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:17,120
Dina...Piangduan...

122
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,160
Who?

123
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:22,120
I’ve never heard of them.

124
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:22,680
Right.

125
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:23,640
I never heard of those names.

126
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:25,680
Stop faking it. How can you not know them?

127
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:28,920
When it comes to Dao Pra Sook, you could tell me scene by scene.

128
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,800
But aren’t they enemies?

129
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,800
Sis, hello.

130
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:36,760
How are you?

131
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:37,880
Oh, I’m fine.

132
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:40,760
Haven’t seen you in twenty-eight years.

133
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:40,960
Oh my God.

134
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,120
Oh my God.

135
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:43,800
I missed you, I missed you.

136
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:46,160
No one ever hired us to see each other.

137
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:47,160
Exactly.

138
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:50,160
They don’t hate each other.

139
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:54,080
But just now it looked like they were about to bite each other’s heads off.

140
00:08:57,240 --> 00:09:00,720
“Imagination.”

141
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:03,440
I’m excited, Sky.

142
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:05,480
Oh please, excited about what?

143
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,880
I’ve been through every kind of production already.

144
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:07,800
As the leading actress?

145
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:09,080
Serving drinks...

146
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:11,080
Back then, I had to earn money to pay for my own studies.

147
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,960
Hello, everyone.

148
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:17,920
Hello.

149
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:19,480
I’m Piangduan.

150
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:23,120
Today, I’ll be leading a workshop on acting for all of you.

151
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:27,120
And I’ll also be the one to decide who gets which role.

152
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:31,520
But before everyone can truly reach the essence of acting…

153
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:35,120
I’d like everyone to go change clothes first, okay?

154
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:37,120
Oh! That must mean we’ll be wearing the costumes for the commercial!

155
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:47,560
Are we filming the commercial at a golf course today?

156
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:51,200
Why do these outfits look like caddy uniforms?

157
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:53,120
Only Tid-Gift looks like a caddy.

158
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:55,440
You and I look like waiters in a grilled fish restaurant.

159
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,440
I remember it, exactly like this.

160
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:59,320
These are just workshop outfits.

161
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:01,440
We’re not diving into any roles yet.

162
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:04,720
Because first, I want everyone to reach the core of acting.

163
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,720
Which is imagination.

164
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:19,720
Sky, are you okay?

165
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:23,240
What? We need to get into the essence of acting, right?

166
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:25,680
There has to be some drama,

167
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:26,880
maybe some crying, stuff like that.

168
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:27,600
Yeah.

169
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:31,600
Good, good. Such energy. But not yet.

170
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:35,760
Right now, we’ll start by walking around the room.

171
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:36,880
Okay, let’s go. Start walking.

172
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:37,920
Walk?

173
00:10:37,920 --> 00:10:39,920
Walk, walk around everywhere.

174
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:51,200
And imagine that right now you are like a fluffy cloud.

175
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:52,760
Huh?

176
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:57,520
We’ll walk floating, soft, like a fluffy cloud.

177
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:07,280
All-New, walk like a fluffy cloud.

178
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:08,160
How do you walk like that?

179
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:10,360
You’re stiff as a rock, like a robot.

180
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:11,280
But a cloud doesn’t walk.

181
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:12,240
Make it flowy, flowy.

182
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:14,760
A fluffy cloud, a cloud floats.

183
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:16,760
Do it, look at Tid-Gift.

184
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:21,000
Next, be ice.

185
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:21,480
Ice...

186
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:23,200
Ice that is about to melt.

187
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:26,320
Walk as if melting, melting.

188
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:29,320
Use your imagination. Melting.

189
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:36,320
Melt, melt, ice melting.

190
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:42,920
Melt, melt.

191
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:45,840
All-New, why aren’t you walking?

192
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:48,640
Ice melts slowly, it has to take its time.

193
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:50,640
Look at Tid-Gift, melting super fast.

194
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:56,200
Next, be a dessert.

195
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:57,600
Dessert.

196
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,720
What kind of dessert?

197
00:11:58,720 --> 00:12:00,680
Any kind of dessert, just try.

198
00:12:00,680 --> 00:12:02,360
Okay, try it.

199
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,320
Dessert...

200
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,320
I said do it.

201
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:08,560
Dessert, dessert, okay.

202
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:18,800
Hey, I already picked Lod Chong, why are you copying me?

203
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:22,360
I’m Singaporean Lod Chong-la, you get it?

204
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:24,240
Look at my skin!

205
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:28,240
Uncle-la, Auntie, Uncle...

206
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:30,240
Great imagination, very good.

207
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:34,480
And what are you?

208
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:37,520
A Thai pudding.

209
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:39,880
Okay, you're not like it, but okay.

210
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:52,920
And this?

211
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:53,920
A Tokyo crepe.

212
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:57,520
Good.

213
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:02,040
And what’s this?

214
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:03,040
Cotton candy roti.

215
00:13:03,920 --> 00:13:04,920
Where’s the cotton candy roti?

216
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:08,800
In my mouth, I’m eating it.

217
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:13,120
You’re supposed to imagine being it, not imagine eating it.

218
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:13,840
There's one more here.

219
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:16,680
No, be a cotton candy roti.

220
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:18,680
I’m a Chinese shortbread.

221
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:20,960
Fine, that works too.

222
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:24,000
Now, be animals.

223
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:28,400
What’s this?

224
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:29,160
A sloth.

225
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:30,200
And what does it look like?

226
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,200
It’s just slow.

227
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:42,280
I can’t take this anymore, can I just go back to flying?

228
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:43,440
They pay us, you know.

229
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:45,920
How much could it even be?

230
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:47,480
I think acting is too hard.

231
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:48,680
Damn, it doesn’t suit me at all.

232
00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:50,680
I’ll just go tell them.

233
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:53,720
120,000 each.

234
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:59,080
Actually, I think we should challenge ourselves sometimes.
Okay, let’s do it.

235
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:03,520
The staff said they’ll split us into two groups.

236
00:14:03,520 --> 00:14:05,920
One group will do the acting workshop with Piangduan.

237
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:08,920
And the other group will do the modeling workshop with Dina.

238
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:12,040
So I don’t have to do acting, right?

239
00:14:12,040 --> 00:14:12,880
In that case, I’ll...

240
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:18,800
I, Chai, and Sky will join the modeling workshop with Dina.

241
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:19,800
Bye.

242
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:24,760
Can I just not do it?

243
00:14:31,680 --> 00:14:35,320
"No one’s going anywhere, you have to stay here."

244
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:39,400
Hey, All-New, Piangduan must’ve heard us talking.

245
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:40,800
She just sent us a message.

246
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:43,520
Huh? Why would she send a message?

247
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:46,040
Isn’t it easier to just walk over and talk?

248
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:50,040
"Sabotage this workshop as I ordered."

249
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:52,120
Who’s that?

250
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:56,840
"Do you remember my bullets?"

251
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:06,160
"Last time, you drove away and I still caught up."

252
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:10,160
"But this time, you’re trapped in a square room...
do you think you can escape?"

253
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:18,560
Peck!

254
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:19,560
Pong!

255
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:34,760
“Shine.”

256
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:39,480
Besides commercials,

257
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,160
Glamorous Airline will also have a photo shoot.

258
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:45,080
I will be your coach today.

259
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:51,600
Before we start, who can tell me what a model is?

260
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:53,320
It’s someone who presents the product.

261
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:54,320
Wrong.

262
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:57,280
It’s a fashion model.

263
00:15:57,280 --> 00:16:00,920
Then why translate it into Thai for me?

264
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:03,680
It’s someone whose character matches the product.

265
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:04,680
Wrong.

266
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:08,040
A model is someone who has to be beautiful and look good.

267
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:12,040
Oh, so that’s why the three of us are here.

268
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:16,560
Or someone unique and exotic.

269
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:20,440
Handsome.

270
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:22,280
Pretty.

271
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:23,120
Different.

272
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:24,120
That’s complete.

273
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:32,880
We have to look good.
If we don’t look good, the product won’t get attention.

274
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:36,000
So what do we have to do...

275
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:39,240
to make the product get attention?

276
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:41,240
Be one with the product.

277
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:42,240
Wrong.

278
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:44,880
We have to understand the product’s character.

279
00:16:44,880 --> 00:16:45,880
Oh my god, wrong.

280
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:49,800
We have to hold the product well and not drop it.

281
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:54,800
Yeah, that’s true. But no, wrong!

282
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:56,880
We have to shine.

283
00:16:56,880 --> 00:16:58,360
We have to glow.

284
00:16:58,360 --> 00:17:01,160
That’s how the product will get attention.

285
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:01,960
Let’s do this.

286
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:03,960
You get the camera, go.

287
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:13,200
The two of you will take a group shot
and let’s see how you steal the spotlight.

288
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:17,200
Do whatever it takes to stand out the most, okay?

289
00:17:17,360 --> 00:17:18,120
Yes.

290
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:18,720
Okay.

291
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:19,720
Alright, let’s go.

292
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:21,080
One, two.

293
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:24,200
Okay, put the photo on the screen.

294
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:28,640
Hey.

295
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:31,600
When did Dina pop up?

296
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:36,600
A good model must know how to steal the scene smoothly like this.

297
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:38,400
Again, one more time.

298
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:39,640
One, two, snap.

299
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:42,800
When did she get in?

300
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:44,880
Ugh, not working, come on.

301
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:45,920
One, two, snap.

302
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:49,960
Whoa, this already looks like a campaign winner.

303
00:17:49,960 --> 00:17:52,960
One last time now.

304
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:54,920
Okay, one, two, snap.

305
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:06,440
How did Dina do that?

306
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,800
No matter how fast, you can’t beat the photographer.

307
00:18:10,560 --> 00:18:11,560
Hey.

308
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:14,640
How did she do it?

309
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:16,640
Because I’m Dina, bitches.

310
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:19,920
I give up.

311
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:28,280
“Emotion.”

312
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:34,520
Why would they want us to sabotage the workshop?

313
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:38,520
Yeah, exactly. Aren’t those people working for Mr. Glam?

314
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:42,720
Why wouldn’t Mr. Glam want his own commercial to turn out good?

315
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:46,000
Or maybe he wants drama in the workshop.

316
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,920
So the commercial will go viral.

317
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:49,600
Get your phone ready.

318
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:51,600
They’ll text us again any minute.

319
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:58,480
"You have received the right to apply for a loan..."

320
00:18:58,480 --> 00:18:59,560
Damn it.

321
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:00,520
Do I have to borrow money now?

322
00:19:00,520 --> 00:19:01,720
No.

323
00:19:01,720 --> 00:19:02,920
This is definitely a scam.

324
00:19:02,920 --> 00:19:03,760
Right.

325
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:05,760
Hey, Chaba, when did you get here?

326
00:19:06,840 --> 00:19:09,400
I came as soon as I heard Kreetha’s stupidity.

327
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:11,400
Don’t even know if the name is Kreetha or Donkree.
You're too dumb.

328
00:19:13,280 --> 00:19:15,800
Are you ready for the next lesson?

329
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:21,440
The next lesson, I believe everyone can do it.

330
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:23,520
That is expressing emotions.

331
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:25,640
Since our shooting time is limited, right?

332
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:27,680
We need to interpret emotions.

333
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:29,480
From a situation we imagine ourselves.

334
00:19:29,480 --> 00:19:32,360
And act it out immediately.

335
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:33,600
What kind of emotion do you want to see?

336
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:34,840
Sadness. Sadness.

337
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:36,560
The way to show sadness is...

338
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:37,160
Crying.

339
00:19:37,160 --> 00:19:38,640
Oh, crying. A lot or a little?

340
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:39,440
Just a little.

341
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:40,000
How many drops?

342
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:40,480
One.

343
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:41,280
From which side?

344
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:42,520
The corner of the eye.

345
00:19:42,520 --> 00:19:43,520
Take a look.

346
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:06,800
Oh my god, Queen of Tears.

347
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,000
Made to order.

348
00:20:10,360 --> 00:20:12,360
Alright, now it’s everyone’s turn.

349
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:23,840
Cry. You’re in so much pain, tears should fall.

350
00:20:23,840 --> 00:20:27,200
No, no. I didn’t tell you to cry.

351
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:30,440
The emotion everyone has to express is...

352
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:31,160
I won’t tell you.

353
00:20:31,160 --> 00:20:32,320
What?

354
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:35,920
You have to interpret it from the situation I’ll give.

355
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:37,920
Oh no, we have to interpret too?

356
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:38,880
This is way too hard.

357
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:39,880
Kreetha is definitely doomed.

358
00:20:40,320 --> 00:20:41,320
I’m winning this campaign for sure.

359
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:43,920
Let’s pretend, okay?

360
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:47,920
Pretend you receive a threatening SMS ordering you to obey.

361
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:49,200
How did you know that?

362
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:50,440
Huh?

363
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:54,120
He means how would we know how to act it?

364
00:20:54,120 --> 00:21:00,120
Just imagine a text comes to your phone.

365
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:07,800
And you read the message.

366
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:12,800
“Don’t let anyone know you’re being threatened, or you’re done.”

367
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:19,880
And then we…

368
00:21:20,040 --> 00:21:24,000
Yes, this face. The face of someone being threatened.

369
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:25,920
No, no, no.

370
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:27,560
Yes, exactly. That face is perfect.

371
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:29,160
Threatened not to tell anyone, right?

372
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:31,920
No, no message is threatening me.

373
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:34,200
Yes, like that. Keep that emotion, just like that.

374
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,680
Keep the emotion, hold onto it.

375
00:21:35,680 --> 00:21:37,040
Immerse yourself in it, immerse yourself.

376
00:21:37,040 --> 00:21:38,360
Keep that energy.

377
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:39,600
Hold it, hold it.

378
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:40,600
You have to truly feel it.

379
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:42,400
You have to truly feel it.

380
00:21:46,520 --> 00:21:47,520
"Don’t show any suspicion."

381
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:54,840
See? That’s suspicious.

382
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:56,480
No, no.

383
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:58,920
Yes, that’s it! That’s amazing!

384
00:21:58,920 --> 00:22:00,400
So good, incredible.

385
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:03,600
That’s great.

386
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:05,600
Do it like this, watch, watch.

387
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:08,200
How did he do that?

388
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,000
How?

389
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:11,600
He's so talented.

390
00:22:15,120 --> 00:22:17,080
Will anyone find out?

391
00:22:17,080 --> 00:22:18,240
They think you’re just acting.

392
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:19,680
No, it’s real.

393
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:20,920
Why are you speaking so loud?

394
00:22:20,920 --> 00:22:23,000
They said no one else can know about this.

395
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:26,960
Oh, then no need to whisper if you’re going to be this loud.

396
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:30,880
Enough. During the break, just don't say anything to anyone.

397
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:34,880
Don’t say a word, zip it. Okay?

398
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:36,200
I’m going to the bathroom real quick.

399
00:22:42,120 --> 00:22:43,120
Are you not telling me something?

400
00:22:46,320 --> 00:22:48,320
Did you secretly take classes with Kru Ngor?

401
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:57,720
"Injure someone here, make sure somebody gets hurt."

402
00:23:01,120 --> 00:23:02,120
Your expression gave it all away.

403
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:05,720
Now, I know you’re really good at acting.

404
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:07,200
You’re great at acting. You’re the best.

405
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:09,440
Are you still not done?

406
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:10,600
How long are you going to rub it in my face?

407
00:23:10,840 --> 00:23:11,840
I’m hurt, damn it.

408
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:13,400
If we don’t follow orders, we’re screwed.

409
00:23:14,680 --> 00:23:15,680
Sorry, Chaba.

410
00:23:18,280 --> 00:23:20,280
Hey! Why did you hit me?

411
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:24,120
What play are you even acting out?

412
00:23:24,120 --> 00:23:25,440
Pla Bu Thong?

413
00:23:25,440 --> 00:23:27,440
Or the Huntsman and the Magic Axe?

414
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:28,440
Then who am I?

415
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:29,640
A tree?

416
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:30,760
So I’ve just been chopped down, huh?

417
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:42,840
Chaba, is acting class fun?

418
00:23:42,840 --> 00:23:46,840
Well...probably not as fun as you guys.

419
00:23:47,320 --> 00:23:51,040
Is it really that tiring?
I saw you drinking water all day.

420
00:23:51,040 --> 00:23:52,600
I want to switch classes.

421
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:54,400
But acting class is already good, right?

422
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:56,800
It’s good, but I want to learn something else too.

423
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:59,080
Or...can we change classmates instead?

424
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:01,600
You mean because Kreetha is dragging the class down, right?

425
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:03,800
It’s not Kreetha, Chai.

426
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:05,880
It’s me who’s the burden.

427
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:07,480
Today, Kreetha was amazing.

428
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:08,760
He acted really well.

429
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:11,800
No, you also have to act by blending yourself into it.

430
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:13,040
Like a “main character,” right?

431
00:24:13,040 --> 00:24:14,720
I meant like a “big body.”

432
00:24:14,720 --> 00:24:15,480
And that is...

433
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:16,480
An encouragement.

434
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:18,680
Oh.

435
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:21,000
Then, just steal the spotlight. You can do it.

436
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:29,600
Do it smoothly, so no one notices.

437
00:24:30,840 --> 00:24:32,840
Yeah, Dina taught that.

438
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:36,520
Wait, you learned this already, right?

439
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:38,520
Did she teach you modeling or teach you freeze tag?

440
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:41,400
Okay, freeze right there.

441
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:44,480
If anyone falls first, I’ll tell Dina to come slap you.

442
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:45,800
I can stand here all day.

443
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:46,560
I can stand here all day too.

444
00:24:46,560 --> 00:24:47,160
Then you stand.

445
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:48,000
I’m standing.

446
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,200
Fine, you stand then.

447
00:24:49,200 --> 00:24:50,200
I can barely stand now.

448
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:54,000
“Improvise.”

449
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:56,560
"Injure someone here, make sure somebody gets hurt."

450
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:02,160
Then...who are we supposed to hurt?

451
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:03,320
I already hit Chaba.

452
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:04,320
How did you hit her?

453
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:05,440
Like this.

454
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:08,800
Do you even understand what “injure” means?

455
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:09,920
I couldn’t do it.

456
00:25:09,920 --> 00:25:12,200
That’s Chaba, how could I hurt her?

457
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:14,200
If you don’t do it, you saw the message, right?

458
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:20,520
I really love this.

459
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:22,760
Are you still immersed in character?

460
00:25:22,760 --> 00:25:25,000
Uh...since when have you been sitting there?

461
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:26,200
I've been here a while.

462
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:27,440
This is really good.

463
00:25:27,440 --> 00:25:29,920
You’ve continued the imagination and built it into a story.

464
00:25:31,920 --> 00:25:33,080
I'm here!

465
00:25:33,080 --> 00:25:35,480
I'm ready to perform live for everyone right here.

466
00:25:35,480 --> 00:25:38,480
A live performance straight from the actor's heart.

467
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:42,080
This is really good too.

468
00:25:42,080 --> 00:25:45,040
An example of being totally fake.

469
00:25:45,040 --> 00:25:47,040
Watch carefully, but don’t copy it.

470
00:25:49,680 --> 00:25:52,760
Alright, next lesson.

471
00:25:52,760 --> 00:25:56,440
I want everyone to create a situation.

472
00:25:56,440 --> 00:25:59,280
Try improvising, just act it out yourselves.

473
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:02,080
Improvise, everything’s real, think it up on the spot.

474
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:04,200
I guess she'll move on from the threatening SMS storyline.

475
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:05,920
We'll continue from the SMS.

476
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:09,000
Say the SMS orders you to hurt your friend, right?

477
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:09,800
Shit!

478
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:10,800
And then, you act it out.

479
00:26:13,280 --> 00:26:15,280
Okay, let’s try.

480
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:18,800
Uh...a knife?

481
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:23,160
Let’s imagine you two have to hurt a friend because of the threat.

482
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:26,440
And you will be the victim.

483
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:27,880
Let’s see how we act in that situation.

484
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:29,360
Alright, ready, let’s go.

485
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:29,960
Start.

486
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:33,680
Hey, Kreetha, are you really going to kill me?

487
00:26:33,680 --> 00:26:34,840
That’s a knife!

488
00:26:34,840 --> 00:26:36,400
No, Chaba, no.

489
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:37,400
Here, take it.

490
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:41,200
Help me! Save me!

491
00:26:45,640 --> 00:26:48,640
"You’ve got the knife, so stab already."

492
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:50,640
Shit, All-New, how did they see us?

493
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:54,560
Yes, that’s very good.

494
00:26:54,560 --> 00:26:57,680
Before stabbing, you even looked left and right.

495
00:26:57,680 --> 00:26:59,680
Stab, go ahead.

496
00:27:03,040 --> 00:27:05,840
Ahhh, Chaba, what are you doing?

497
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:07,440
I didn’t do anything.

498
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:09,000
Then let go of my hand and stab me already.

499
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:09,960
You’re too strong.

500
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:10,960
I guess I won't die.

501
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:16,880
Now, imagine you fight back, and then you turn and stab.

502
00:27:18,120 --> 00:27:19,520
Alright, then.

503
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:22,040
Stab! Yes.

504
00:27:22,040 --> 00:27:23,040
Oh!

505
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:24,440
Cramp!

506
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:24,840
What?

507
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:25,920
A cramp in my hand!

508
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:29,720
I can’t pick it up, oh no!

509
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:30,720
What should I do?

510
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:34,120
Here, I got it.

511
00:27:34,200 --> 00:27:35,200
What the hell, man?

512
00:27:35,840 --> 00:27:38,120
Grab the knife, grab the knife!

513
00:27:38,120 --> 00:27:40,200
I’m ready to die, I accept it.

514
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:42,200
Take care of my mom and my sister.

515
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:44,000
I said I don’t want it!

516
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:54,880
Shit, Chaba.

517
00:27:56,760 --> 00:28:00,040
“Obstacles.”

518
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:04,080
Alright, the next lesson.

519
00:28:04,080 --> 00:28:10,360
How do we stay beautiful at all times, even when we face obstacles?

520
00:28:10,360 --> 00:28:13,040
Oh, is that even possible?

521
00:28:13,040 --> 00:28:15,040
It is. Try it.

522
00:28:18,680 --> 00:28:20,680
Oh, oh, I’m cold.

523
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:21,880
That’s not the point.

524
00:28:21,880 --> 00:28:22,880
I said pose.

525
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:25,080
Don’t act cold.

526
00:28:25,680 --> 00:28:26,640
Beautiful.

527
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:27,640
Handsome.

528
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:28,600
Fabulous.

529
00:28:28,600 --> 00:28:29,600
Face it.

530
00:28:51,120 --> 00:28:52,600
Oh my god.

531
00:28:53,760 --> 00:28:57,760
You must take that obstacle and turn it into a prop.

532
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:02,640
Use it to enhance yourself. Watch.

533
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:31,440
Wow, amazing!

534
00:29:31,440 --> 00:29:35,440
I wonder if the acting class has lessons like this too.

535
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:36,880
I really want to know.

536
00:29:36,880 --> 00:29:39,560
What does Piangduan teach in her acting class?

537
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:41,280
She looks very talented, doesn’t she?

538
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:43,120
I just don’t understand.

539
00:29:43,120 --> 00:29:46,840
Why bring in something so old like this?

540
00:29:46,840 --> 00:29:50,520
It’s useless, just standing there, blocking my sight.

541
00:29:50,520 --> 00:29:52,920
Having only me is enough.

542
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:56,920
Dina, calm down. We won’t mention it again.

543
00:29:57,760 --> 00:30:00,840
Choose. This or that?

544
00:30:00,840 --> 00:30:02,480
Dina.

545
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:06,320
Good. Staff, take care of it.

546
00:30:06,880 --> 00:30:10,240
Dina, I don’t know what beef you two had.

547
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:12,120
But please don’t use violence.

548
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:14,040
Yes, don’t fight with Piangduan.

549
00:30:14,040 --> 00:30:16,040
If there’s an issue, let’s talk it out calmly.

550
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:20,040
That’s right, no need to spill blood.

551
00:30:20,680 --> 00:30:23,200
What? Piangduan what?

552
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:24,200
This fan!

553
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:28,720
See? Old, broken, useless. Take it away.

554
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:34,320
Go practice with the fan on.

555
00:30:34,320 --> 00:30:35,320
Yes, yes.

556
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:38,120
Clear your face, get your hair out of the way.

557
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:41,480
Smile, smile, fight against it.

558
00:30:41,480 --> 00:30:43,880
You can do it. Smile.

559
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:44,160
Chaba.

560
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:44,960
Chaba.

561
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:47,480
I’m sorry, stay strong.

562
00:30:47,480 --> 00:30:47,760
Chaba.

563
00:30:48,080 --> 00:30:49,080
Chaba.

564
00:30:51,760 --> 00:30:52,760
Who turned off the lights?

565
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:54,280
Chaba.

566
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:56,080
Is that the voice of an angel?

567
00:30:56,080 --> 00:30:58,240
An angel has come to take me away, hasn’t she?

568
00:30:58,240 --> 00:30:59,480
Chaba, don’t die.

569
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:01,280
Don’t be sad, All-New.

570
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:02,800
But you must remember.

571
00:31:02,800 --> 00:31:04,800
You’re the one who caused my death.

572
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:09,360
Chaba, no!

573
00:31:10,440 --> 00:31:12,720
No, Chaba!

574
00:31:12,720 --> 00:31:13,120
Chaba!

575
00:31:13,720 --> 00:31:14,720
Chaba!

576
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:17,200
No!

577
00:31:23,440 --> 00:31:25,120
That was amazing.

578
00:31:25,120 --> 00:31:27,120
Amazing. Perfect.

579
00:31:33,640 --> 00:31:34,640
A fake knife?

580
00:31:35,040 --> 00:31:37,600
Who would use a real knife for acting?

581
00:31:37,600 --> 00:31:40,280
But everyone acted so well, it was absolutely perfect.

582
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:44,280
Everyone was great. I’m very, very proud of you.

583
00:31:44,840 --> 00:31:47,480
Especially you, you are so talented.

584
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:48,480
You can do anything.

585
00:31:49,120 --> 00:31:50,120
Thank you.

586
00:31:52,160 --> 00:31:53,480
Hey, Chaba!

587
00:31:53,480 --> 00:31:55,640
Okay, okay, that’s enough.
Stop acting, we know you’re good.

588
00:31:55,640 --> 00:31:58,040
Oh, why is my heart racing?

589
00:31:58,040 --> 00:31:59,040
Chaba.

590
00:32:01,960 --> 00:32:02,600
What’s wrong?

591
00:32:02,600 --> 00:32:04,240
The tea...

592
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:04,880
Huh?

593
00:32:04,880 --> 00:32:06,080
What’s wrong with the tea?

594
00:32:06,080 --> 00:32:08,080
The tea was poisoned!

595
00:32:08,080 --> 00:32:10,720
The tea had diet pills in it.

596
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:14,720
Oh my god, so you drank diet tea,
that’s why your heart is racing?

597
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:18,800
Oh no, take her to the hospital right now! Hurry!

598
00:32:19,720 --> 00:32:20,720
Go, let’s go!

599
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:23,320
Chaba!

600
00:32:23,640 --> 00:32:24,640
What's this?

601
00:32:25,640 --> 00:32:29,120
Because we understand what it means to wait.

602
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:31,600
It’s not just about reaching the destination.

603
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:35,600
It’s about caring for every important beat of the heart.

604
00:32:35,960 --> 00:32:36,960
What are you all doing?

605
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:42,520
Dina asked us to memorize the script,
so she can teach us more techniques.

606
00:32:42,520 --> 00:32:44,520
Oh, really? Let me see.

607
00:32:45,720 --> 00:32:46,720
Okay.

608
00:32:49,520 --> 00:32:53,080
Because we understand what it means to wait.

609
00:32:53,080 --> 00:32:55,400
It’s not just about reaching the destination.

610
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:59,400
It’s about caring for every important beat of the heart.

611
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:02,240
Honestly, I’ve memorized it for a while already.

612
00:33:04,880 --> 00:33:08,880
But I don’t think they’ll want you to say it this plain.

613
00:33:09,760 --> 00:33:10,480
Really?

614
00:33:10,480 --> 00:33:12,800
Because a commercial has both a long version

615
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:15,120
and a short version, right?

616
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:18,160
I think Dina will probably want you to say it quickly.

617
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:20,480
For the fifteen-second commercial.

618
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:23,720
Fifteen seconds? Just this much already takes ten seconds.

619
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:26,720
But if you know the technique, you can do it in only three.

620
00:33:29,520 --> 00:33:30,880
Because we understand what it means to wait.

621
00:33:30,880 --> 00:33:32,000
It’s not just about reaching the destination.

622
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:34,000
It’s about caring for every important beat of the heart.

623
00:33:40,600 --> 00:33:42,320
How did you do that? Amazing!

624
00:33:42,320 --> 00:33:45,320
It’s like an editor sped up your voice in post-production.

625
00:33:47,080 --> 00:33:48,800
Do you want me to teach you?

626
00:33:48,800 --> 00:33:51,600
My kid went to the hospital, so I’m free.

627
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:52,720
Who went to the hospital?

628
00:33:52,720 --> 00:33:55,720
I don’t have much time.
Do you want it or not?

629
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:59,160
Please accept us as your students.

630
00:34:00,120 --> 00:34:01,120
Please help us.

631
00:34:09,360 --> 00:34:11,400
“Commercial Speech.”

632
00:34:11,400 --> 00:34:13,240
Because we understand what it means to wait.

633
00:34:13,240 --> 00:34:14,920
It’s not just about reaching the destination.

634
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:16,920
It’s about caring for every important beat of the heart.

635
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:19,320
Huh?

636
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:23,760
Did I teach you to speak this fast?

637
00:34:23,760 --> 00:34:24,760
No.

638
00:34:24,760 --> 00:34:28,160
It’s just that Piangduan taught us this technique.

639
00:34:28,160 --> 00:34:29,440
Yes, Piangduan said that

640
00:34:29,440 --> 00:34:32,440
you wanted us to learn this ad-reading skill.

641
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:41,920
Yes, I want them to know this skill.

642
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:47,400
But it has to be me, Dina, who teaches them, not her.

643
00:34:48,560 --> 00:34:50,880
What do you call that in Thai?

644
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:57,360
Oh, “sticking your nose into other people's business” Oh dear, can I say?

645
00:34:57,360 --> 00:34:59,960
No, this is the right one...

646
00:34:59,960 --> 00:35:02,960
"Nosy." Can I say that?

647
00:35:06,040 --> 00:35:07,040
Dina.

648
00:35:08,680 --> 00:35:09,520
Dina.

649
00:35:09,520 --> 00:35:10,480
Oops.

650
00:35:10,480 --> 00:35:11,480
Oops, sorry.

651
00:35:12,120 --> 00:35:13,120
It’s a habit.

652
00:35:13,160 --> 00:35:14,760
Uh, where were we?

653
00:35:14,760 --> 00:35:18,760
Dina, you don’t mind, right, that we followed what Piangduan taught?

654
00:35:20,320 --> 00:35:23,760
No. Why would I mind?

655
00:35:23,760 --> 00:35:25,240
I’m okay.

656
00:35:25,240 --> 00:35:27,680
Right? Because Piangduan is really, really good.

657
00:35:27,680 --> 00:35:28,680
Yes.

658
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:30,320
Thank you so much.

659
00:35:31,680 --> 00:35:34,440
I didn’t outshine you, did I, Dina?

660
00:35:34,440 --> 00:35:37,480
This should be about teaching together, right?

661
00:35:37,480 --> 00:35:39,120
Well...

662
00:35:39,120 --> 00:35:41,800
You teach, I teach, same same.

663
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:45,200
It’s all the same. We are a team.

664
00:35:45,200 --> 00:35:49,200
But actually, I'm not just going to teach this.

665
00:35:49,760 --> 00:35:53,760
Because our commercial will go worldwide.

666
00:35:54,080 --> 00:35:59,040
And if we only say the slogan in Thai, it’s nothing special.

667
00:35:59,040 --> 00:36:05,040
Honestly, I understand if you're only good at this level.

668
00:36:06,480 --> 00:36:07,680
Well, that's true.

669
00:36:07,680 --> 00:36:11,680
Because I don’t usually teach beyond what’s necessary.

670
00:36:15,080 --> 00:36:16,600
Do you think they’re starting a war?

671
00:36:16,600 --> 00:36:17,560
Of course.

672
00:36:17,560 --> 00:36:19,440
Kids.

673
00:36:19,440 --> 00:36:21,440
Do you think it’s necessary?

674
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:26,280
See? Now they’ve dragged us into the fight.

675
00:36:26,280 --> 00:36:30,280
Uh, excuse me, I think all of us

676
00:36:30,640 --> 00:36:34,640
will definitely use what both of you taught us.

677
00:36:37,880 --> 00:36:41,760
Everyone, repeat after me.

678
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:43,480
We truly understand what it means to wait.

679
00:36:43,480 --> 00:36:45,800
This is not just about bringing you to your destination.

680
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:49,800
It is about caring for every precious beat of your heart.

681
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:52,840
What? What the heck was that?

682
00:36:52,840 --> 00:36:53,640
What?

683
00:36:53,640 --> 00:36:54,640
Oops.

684
00:36:55,600 --> 00:36:58,360
No one repeated it.

685
00:36:58,360 --> 00:36:59,360
Hang in there, Dina.

686
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:09,000
Step out, one person, and repeat what I've just said.

687
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:11,000
Sky. You should do it.

688
00:37:11,320 --> 00:37:12,160
What’s your name?

689
00:37:12,160 --> 00:37:13,160
I'm Sky.

690
00:37:13,240 --> 00:37:17,240
Oh, that’s just the name I was going to give my child.

691
00:37:18,720 --> 00:37:22,720
Perfect, because most people named Sky are good-looking.

692
00:37:23,320 --> 00:37:24,320
Go change your name.

693
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:26,920
Okay, repeat what I've just said.

694
00:37:28,280 --> 00:37:31,280
Please mind the gap between the train and platform.

695
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:38,360
“Interpretation.”

696
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:44,040
Oh, the doctor said you can join class again now?

697
00:37:44,040 --> 00:37:45,040
Yes.

698
00:37:45,040 --> 00:37:46,360
I see.

699
00:37:46,360 --> 00:37:49,240
But why does everyone have to attend all at once?

700
00:37:49,240 --> 00:37:51,120
Because Dina had urgent business.

701
00:37:51,120 --> 00:37:53,120
So we’ll study with Piangduan first.

702
00:37:54,080 --> 00:37:56,600
In the end, you always need me.

703
00:37:56,600 --> 00:37:58,440
Excuse me, what?

704
00:37:58,440 --> 00:38:01,480
Oh, um, this is the final lesson.

705
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:03,680
Let’s move on to the final lesson now.

706
00:38:03,680 --> 00:38:07,320
I want everyone to practice interpreting emotions and feelings.

707
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:09,640
Because sometimes, even if the word is the same,

708
00:38:09,640 --> 00:38:11,600
we can interpret it in many different ways.

709
00:38:11,600 --> 00:38:14,600
For example, the word Ouch.

710
00:38:14,600 --> 00:38:17,320
Say it for me in ten different styles.

711
00:38:17,320 --> 00:38:21,320
Show me how Ouch can be used. Start.

712
00:38:22,640 --> 00:38:25,320
Ouch, like when you kick the table.

713
00:38:25,320 --> 00:38:28,080
Oh, good. What else?

714
00:38:28,080 --> 00:38:34,160
Ouch, like when someone asks me out on a date, but I’m stuck with a flight.

715
00:38:34,160 --> 00:38:37,760
That’s good too. What else?

716
00:38:37,760 --> 00:38:40,560
Ouch, ouch.

717
00:38:40,560 --> 00:38:43,480
This is like when I’ve got four or five flings,

718
00:38:43,480 --> 00:38:47,000
and they almost find out I’m double-dating.

719
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:49,440
Alright, that works. What else?

720
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:53,440
Ouch, ouch, ouch, ouch.

721
00:38:54,840 --> 00:38:55,800
Uh...this one is like...

722
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:58,120
No, no, no, that one we don’t need.

723
00:38:58,120 --> 00:38:59,640
I think everyone already knows.

724
00:38:59,640 --> 00:39:01,880
But I don’t get it.

725
00:39:01,880 --> 00:39:04,880
Ouch...wait until after class.

726
00:39:04,880 --> 00:39:06,880
If you want to know, I’ll teach you.

727
00:39:08,280 --> 00:39:10,280
Anything else?

728
00:39:10,280 --> 00:39:11,760
Ouch.

729
00:39:11,760 --> 00:39:15,760
This one is like being annoyed at a friend who answers too well.

730
00:39:16,480 --> 00:39:17,480
That’s very good.

731
00:39:18,560 --> 00:39:23,640
Ouch, like forgetting you had to go grab something.

732
00:39:23,640 --> 00:39:26,760
Then, I’ll just step outside to get something.

733
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:30,160
In the meantime, think of more Ouch ideas.

734
00:39:30,160 --> 00:39:33,160
Make them sharp and clear.
I’ll listen when I get back.

735
00:39:36,120 --> 00:39:37,520
Ouch, but clearly.

736
00:39:37,520 --> 00:39:39,800
Sky, you try.

737
00:39:39,800 --> 00:39:40,920
I can’t.

738
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:42,200
You can.

739
00:39:42,200 --> 00:39:43,440
What? I can’t.

740
00:39:43,440 --> 00:39:46,440
I’ve seen you do it...Ouch with ten vocal runs.

741
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:49,080
Ouch with ten vocal runs?

742
00:39:49,080 --> 00:39:54,440
Ohhh, like this?

743
00:39:54,440 --> 00:39:57,160
Yes, like chanting.

744
00:39:57,160 --> 00:40:03,200
Oh oh oh oh oh oh oh oh oh ouch!

745
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:04,200
Like Ariana Grande.

746
00:40:07,840 --> 00:40:09,000
Like this?

747
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:11,120
That’s great. Okay, then...

748
00:40:11,120 --> 00:40:12,760
Ouch, enough.

749
00:40:12,760 --> 00:40:15,040
Your turn. I’ve done it until my throat’s about to burst.

750
00:40:15,040 --> 00:40:15,960
Freeloading off your friend.

751
00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:17,760
Hey, I don’t feel well.

752
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:18,880
Do it for me.

753
00:40:18,880 --> 00:40:22,880
One more time, clearly. A strong, clear Ouch.

754
00:40:22,960 --> 00:40:24,960
Since you’re sick...

755
00:40:34,440 --> 00:40:35,760
Hey, that’s stylish.

756
00:40:35,760 --> 00:40:37,400
A clear Ouch that comes from right here.

757
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:39,160
But the sound came from over there.

758
00:40:39,160 --> 00:40:40,160
That wasn’t my voice.

759
00:40:41,200 --> 00:40:43,800
But it sounded like someone in pain.

760
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:44,680
Someone in pain...

761
00:40:44,680 --> 00:40:55,680
Ouch, ouch! Someone put glass shards in my shoe, ouch!

762
00:40:57,320 --> 00:40:58,320
Whoa.

763
00:41:04,720 --> 00:41:07,040
Oh! How are you feeling?

764
00:41:07,040 --> 00:41:08,040
It hurts.

765
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:12,160
Oh no, what happened?

766
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:14,640
I don’t know, someone put broken glass in my shoe.

767
00:41:17,880 --> 00:41:20,160
You want me to say this, right?

768
00:41:20,160 --> 00:41:21,680
Do you think I’m stupid?

769
00:41:21,680 --> 00:41:24,120
Do you think I don’t know it was you?

770
00:41:24,120 --> 00:41:27,000
I don't know anything about this.

771
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:29,520
Oh please, said you had urgent business and rushed out.

772
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:31,520
Your “business” was to pick on me, wasn’t it?

773
00:41:31,520 --> 00:41:35,440
No, I already told you I didn’t do it.

774
00:41:35,440 --> 00:41:38,320
There are more people who hate you than you think.

775
00:41:38,320 --> 00:41:39,920
And one of them is you, right?

776
00:41:39,920 --> 00:41:43,920
I already said I didn’t do it.

777
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:49,760
I’m tired of acting.

778
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:51,760
Yes.

779
00:41:51,760 --> 00:41:54,760
I hate you.

780
00:41:54,760 --> 00:41:56,480
But this time it wasn’t me.

781
00:41:56,480 --> 00:41:59,840
Not you? Oh, like that time, right?

782
00:41:59,840 --> 00:42:03,200
When you put broken glass in your own shoe and blamed me.

783
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:06,760
Yes, that time I did it.

784
00:42:06,760 --> 00:42:11,760
But now? Please.
We're so old our faces are Botox-proof.

785
00:42:11,760 --> 00:42:12,880
Why would I bother?

786
00:42:12,880 --> 00:42:16,440
Will you admit it nicely, or admit it through tears?

787
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:18,680
Oh my god.

788
00:42:18,680 --> 00:42:20,800
That line is ancient.

789
00:42:20,800 --> 00:42:22,800
You're afraid people won’t realize you’re old?

790
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:29,440
Thanks for holding her.

791
00:42:32,160 --> 00:42:34,160
Go hold her instead.

792
00:42:35,640 --> 00:42:36,640
I’m here.

793
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:40,240
I’m here, wait for me.

794
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:43,560
I’m here, I’m coming.

795
00:42:43,560 --> 00:42:46,960
Hey, stop. Stay right there.

796
00:42:46,960 --> 00:42:50,280
Piangduan, let’s go one-on-one.

797
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:51,280
Don’t!

798
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:53,920
So tough, Piangduan?

799
00:42:54,960 --> 00:42:55,960
Tough enough.

800
00:43:03,760 --> 00:43:06,200
Can you stop slapping each other now?

801
00:43:06,200 --> 00:43:08,200
My face is numb already.

802
00:43:10,040 --> 00:43:12,280
All-New, what should we do?

803
00:43:12,280 --> 00:43:15,760
This might actually be the work of Peck and Pong.

804
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:17,440
Someone’s already been hurt.

805
00:43:17,440 --> 00:43:19,440
We have to tell the truth, so everyone knows it wasn’t Dina.

806
00:43:22,400 --> 00:43:23,160
Okay.

807
00:43:23,160 --> 00:43:24,160
Okay what?

808
00:43:25,200 --> 00:43:27,200
Stop, stop, stop!

809
00:43:28,840 --> 00:43:30,400
Dina didn’t do it.

810
00:43:30,400 --> 00:43:32,480
Because I didn’t follow the SMS orders.

811
00:43:32,480 --> 00:43:36,480
So they blamed Piangduan instead.

812
00:43:37,800 --> 00:43:39,600
Wait, did you feed the kids that script?

813
00:43:39,600 --> 00:43:42,840
What? I have no idea, what SMS?

814
00:43:42,840 --> 00:43:43,960
Huh?

815
00:43:43,960 --> 00:43:46,560
Why? I don’t know anything about it.

816
00:43:46,560 --> 00:43:49,480
See? The kids acted really well.

817
00:43:49,480 --> 00:43:51,480
This one kept the character perfectly.

818
00:43:53,280 --> 00:43:55,280
Okay, okay, cut, cut, cut!

819
00:43:56,080 --> 00:43:59,200
Man, we were just hitting the climax.

820
00:43:59,200 --> 00:44:03,200
And then suddenly the SMS boy popped in out of nowhere...
I didn't know what to do.

821
00:44:04,280 --> 00:44:06,280
Great job, everyone.

822
00:44:08,440 --> 00:44:10,280
What is all this?

823
00:44:10,280 --> 00:44:12,200
It’s your final lesson.

824
00:44:12,200 --> 00:44:15,120
Do you see now? To have good acting…

825
00:44:15,120 --> 00:44:18,720
we must fully believe in the situation.

826
00:44:18,720 --> 00:44:20,720
Then what about the wound on the foot?

827
00:44:23,000 --> 00:44:25,160
It’s been used for generations, and it still works.

828
00:44:25,160 --> 00:44:27,160
And what about all the hating each other all day?

829
00:44:29,840 --> 00:44:31,840
That’s showbiz.

830
00:44:34,520 --> 00:44:36,440
Everyone did really well.

831
00:44:36,440 --> 00:44:38,160
Especially, you.

832
00:44:38,160 --> 00:44:41,320
You should go act in an action movie.

833
00:44:41,320 --> 00:44:43,880
But that SMS boy...

834
00:44:43,880 --> 00:44:45,880
wasn’t very good. You're not convincing at all.

835
00:44:48,200 --> 00:44:51,160
I want everyone to remember…

836
00:44:51,160 --> 00:44:55,160
everything both of us taught you today.

837
00:44:55,760 --> 00:44:59,760
And take it all...and use it in the filming of our commercial.

838
00:45:01,240 --> 00:45:03,840
The spirit and essence of the two of us...

839
00:45:03,840 --> 00:45:05,840
will live on in this commercial of yours.

840
00:45:08,640 --> 00:45:09,640
Give it your all, everyone.

841
00:45:10,200 --> 00:45:12,200
Strong. We can do it.

842
00:45:13,880 --> 00:45:14,880
Strong.

843
00:45:15,360 --> 00:45:16,360
We can do it.

844
00:45:17,240 --> 00:45:18,240
We can do it.

845
00:45:18,280 --> 00:45:19,280
We can do it.

846
00:45:19,800 --> 00:45:20,800
We can do it.

847
00:45:21,200 --> 00:45:22,200
We can do it.

848
00:45:22,280 --> 00:45:23,280
Loud and clear, we can do it.

849
00:45:24,160 --> 00:45:26,160
We can do it. Yay!

850
00:45:39,480 --> 00:45:43,080
"This is your last chance before everyone goes home."

851
00:45:43,080 --> 00:45:47,080
"Complete the final mission, which is..."

852
00:45:50,360 --> 00:45:51,440
Why don't you read the rest?

853
00:45:51,440 --> 00:45:52,480
I don’t want to see it.

854
00:45:52,480 --> 00:45:54,840
What if it says we have to kill someone, then what?

855
00:45:54,840 --> 00:45:56,200
Why are you guessing?

856
00:45:56,200 --> 00:45:57,800
Just read the message to the end first.

857
00:45:57,800 --> 00:45:59,800
Then you’ll know if it really says to kill.

858
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:06,760
"You have overdue payments for two months."

859
00:46:06,760 --> 00:46:08,760
"The network will now suspend your phone service."

860
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:14,200
Oh, come on, why cut me off right now?

861
00:46:14,200 --> 00:46:16,600
Then how will we know what they want us to do?

862
00:46:16,600 --> 00:46:17,760
There’s no way to know.

863
00:46:17,760 --> 00:46:19,240
We can’t contact them any other way.

864
00:46:19,240 --> 00:46:20,040
Exactly.

865
00:46:20,040 --> 00:46:21,080
This is such bad luck.

866
00:46:21,080 --> 00:46:22,200
No, it’s actually good luck.

867
00:46:22,720 --> 00:46:23,480
Huh?

868
00:46:23,480 --> 00:46:26,400
If they can’t contact us, that means we don’t know.

869
00:46:26,400 --> 00:46:27,520
And…

870
00:46:27,520 --> 00:46:30,200
we don’t have to follow their orders.

871
00:46:30,200 --> 00:46:36,200
So does that mean we have to go find them,
just to know what they want us to do?

872
00:46:37,800 --> 00:46:41,800
Sometimes I wonder how I even became friends with you.

873
00:46:42,520 --> 00:46:44,040
Didn’t you drink milk as a kid?

874
00:46:44,800 --> 00:46:45,800
I drank some.

875
00:46:48,880 --> 00:46:50,880
Then where am I supposed to get money to pay for the internet?

876
00:47:02,200 --> 00:47:05,280
Okay, we're about to shoot in a bit, everyone. Be prepared.

877
00:47:05,280 --> 00:47:06,280
I'm ready.

878
00:47:27,800 --> 00:47:29,600
Because we...

879
00:47:29,600 --> 00:47:31,560
understand...

880
00:47:31,560 --> 00:47:33,080
what it means...

881
00:47:33,080 --> 00:47:34,080
to wait...

882
00:47:46,080 --> 00:47:47,080
Oh.

883
00:47:48,760 --> 00:47:52,400
It’s not just about reaching the destination.

884
00:47:52,400 --> 00:47:54,560
It's about caring...

885
00:47:54,560 --> 00:47:56,560
for every precious beat of your heart.

886
00:48:18,960 --> 00:48:19,240
Guys!

887
00:48:19,920 --> 00:48:20,920
Guys!

888
00:48:22,360 --> 00:48:24,360
Piangduan is calling!

889
00:48:25,480 --> 00:48:27,000
Hello, everyone.

890
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:28,000
The commercial is out now.

891
00:48:32,720 --> 00:48:34,400
I’ve already seen the full version.

892
00:48:34,400 --> 00:48:37,280
Because I joined in a little myself.

893
00:48:37,280 --> 00:48:39,000
So the director sent it to me first.

894
00:48:39,000 --> 00:48:42,000
I called to praise you all, you acted really, really well.

895
00:48:44,080 --> 00:48:45,080
It was me, I was the best.

896
00:48:46,480 --> 00:48:48,760
It should already be up on the Glamorous Airline website.

897
00:48:48,760 --> 00:48:50,480
Go check out your own work.

898
00:48:50,480 --> 00:48:51,480
Great job, everyone.

899
00:48:52,320 --> 00:48:53,320
Thank you.

900
00:48:55,040 --> 00:48:55,800
All-New, play it, hurry.

901
00:48:56,360 --> 00:48:57,360
Play it.

902
00:48:59,760 --> 00:49:00,760
Oh, here it comes!

903
00:49:06,640 --> 00:49:09,160
Because we understand what it means to wait.

904
00:49:13,960 --> 00:49:15,480
See you soon, Mom!

905
00:49:26,560 --> 00:49:27,760
It’s not...

906
00:49:27,760 --> 00:49:28,480
just...

907
00:49:28,480 --> 00:49:29,800
about reaching the destination.

908
00:49:33,840 --> 00:49:36,720
It’s about caring for every important beat of the heart.

909
00:49:36,720 --> 00:49:37,720
Mom!

910
00:49:44,000 --> 00:49:46,000
It's about caring for every precious beat of your heart.

911
00:50:02,600 --> 00:50:03,160
That was it?

912
00:50:03,160 --> 00:50:04,160
Hey!

913
00:50:04,840 --> 00:50:06,200
I think we acted way more than this, didn’t we?

914
00:50:06,640 --> 00:50:08,440
Why is my part just the word “just”?

915
00:50:08,440 --> 00:50:09,920
Why is my face not there at all?

916
00:50:10,160 --> 00:50:11,440
But Chai’s voice is the loudest.

917
00:50:11,520 --> 00:50:12,760
But there’s no face!

918
00:50:13,000 --> 00:50:16,080
Didn’t Piangduan say she only cameoed a little?

919
00:50:16,080 --> 00:50:18,560
Excuse me, you’re basically the lead actress now.

920
00:50:18,560 --> 00:50:20,560
And we’re just extras.

921
00:50:21,280 --> 00:50:23,000
That’s showbiz.

922
00:50:23,360 --> 00:50:25,760
And that scene we shot for three hours?

923
00:50:25,760 --> 00:50:28,480
Our hair had to be blowing, eighteen fans were on us.

924
00:50:28,480 --> 00:50:30,200
And in that scene, I looked gorgeous.

925
00:50:30,200 --> 00:50:34,200
My hair was flying, flying, flying like this.

926
00:50:34,360 --> 00:50:35,360
But it’s not there at all.

927
00:50:36,200 --> 00:50:38,200
That’s it? Play it again.

928
00:50:38,560 --> 00:50:39,560
Yeah, play it again.

929
00:50:41,480 --> 00:50:45,520
So now you know, the best player in the game isn't me, Dina.

930
00:50:45,920 --> 00:50:48,800
But it's Piangduan.

931
00:50:48,800 --> 00:50:52,800
Do you wanna borrow this, Glamorous Airline's kids?

932
00:50:57,920 --> 00:50:59,520
Because we understand what it means to wait.

933
00:50:59,520 --> 00:51:01,440
It's not just about the destination.

934
00:51:01,440 --> 00:51:03,240
Reaching...reaching...

935
00:51:03,240 --> 00:51:04,280
Reaching the destination.

936
00:51:04,280 --> 00:51:05,760
They left "reaching" behind.

937
00:51:05,760 --> 00:51:07,640
It's not just about reaching the destination.

938
00:51:07,640 --> 00:51:08,640
I didn't say it wrong!

939
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:14,000
I understand if you, Piangdao...

940
00:51:14,000 --> 00:51:16,680
Wait, Piangduan, Piangduan.

941
00:51:16,680 --> 00:51:18,680
Dina and Piangduan, okay.

942
00:51:20,920 --> 00:51:23,080
The photographer is handsome.

943
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:24,560
I'd like to have a photographer like this.

944
00:51:26,360 --> 00:51:28,080
It's not just about reaching the destination.

945
00:51:28,080 --> 00:51:30,600
It’s about caring for every important beat of the heart.

946
00:51:30,600 --> 00:51:33,760
Do it again. It's obvious that you all were reading it.

947
00:51:33,760 --> 00:51:34,760
Make it smoother.

948
00:51:35,600 --> 00:51:37,600
I'm here. It's Chaba.

949
00:51:41,400 --> 00:51:42,400
It's broken.

950
00:51:44,160 --> 00:51:45,160
The tire is flat.

951
00:51:46,040 --> 00:51:47,040
It's broken.

952
00:51:47,720 --> 00:51:48,440
It's totally broken.

953
00:51:48,440 --> 00:51:51,480
I'm here. I'm here!

954
00:51:51,480 --> 00:51:52,640
Wait for me!

955
00:51:52,640 --> 00:51:53,640
I'll stop them!

956
00:51:54,520 --> 00:51:55,520
Which way should I go?

957
00:51:56,560 --> 00:51:59,080
Wait, I'm coming!

958
00:52:02,400 --> 00:52:03,400
So what's next?

959
00:52:04,200 --> 00:52:05,200
Cut!

960
00:52:07,240 --> 00:52:08,200
Alright!

961
00:52:08,200 --> 00:52:09,200
Here we go!

962
00:52:11,120 --> 00:52:13,800
I think you two should stop.

963
00:52:13,800 --> 00:52:15,800
My face is all numb.

964
00:52:18,680 --> 00:52:19,680
So?

965
00:52:22,360 --> 00:52:24,360
I don't know when we started to smile.

966
00:52:26,040 --> 00:52:29,080
Today, I want to find one person to join me at the booth.

967
00:52:29,080 --> 00:52:30,920
Tid-Gift, you come with me today.

968
00:52:30,920 --> 00:52:31,200
Huh?

969
00:52:31,640 --> 00:52:34,480
Even Glamorous Airline is here at the booth?

970
00:52:34,480 --> 00:52:36,480
Or is it because their sales are dropping?

971
00:52:38,080 --> 00:52:39,080
Oh!

972
00:52:40,160 --> 00:52:41,160
Are you okay?

973
00:52:41,320 --> 00:52:43,520
Book your trip now and you’ll get a stylish, trendy T-shirt.

974
00:52:43,520 --> 00:52:44,560
Book now, book now.

975
00:52:44,560 --> 00:52:45,360
Please, right this way.

976
00:52:45,360 --> 00:52:48,080
Damn, such a smooth seller.
How are we supposed to compete with that?

977
00:52:49,160 --> 00:52:51,560
Are you sure you want to come back and fight again?

978
00:52:51,560 --> 00:52:53,000
I shouldn’t run away.

979
00:52:53,000 --> 00:52:55,920
I’m ready to come back and hunt you down, Glam.
